{
  "stem": "9899.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father hit upon this stone of his son, of Emmanuel, my brother who had died, and he had to drag that and put it on the-- on the street and bang on it and-- and-- and with other Jews, perform that horrible thing.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all the-- all the streets were paved with the [? lapids-- ?] is it called in English?-- of all the Jews that had perished and were buried in the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the cemetery was completely destroyed in this horrible manner.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like a Machiavellic-- like a Kafkan book or situation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- they invented the most horrible and horrifying things for the Jewish people to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then one day, we were all taken to the [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Janowska ?] prison because my father was declared a saboteur, that he was sabotaging his work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was not true.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow, somebody said he was guilty of that, and we were-- and they were going to condemn him to be killed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother, in desperation, took some of the jewels of the family and run to the-- to the camp, and we were retained there for several days.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at that time, there was no one to talk to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she went to the commandant and gave him a large diamond in exchange, and he accepted to-- to leave us alone.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we escaped from that horror.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let us go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Went back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were only allowed to return to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The beatings, yes, the beatings, the killings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was witnessing already for several months the destruction of humanity in the vilest ways, but nothing compared to what yet would come.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
